WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.100
A clear June morning on the Oakland estuary. The fleet waits at the docks.

00:00:05.100 --> 00:00:13.100
We gather at the yacht club for the morning briefing, life vests on and ready to go.

00:00:13.100 --> 00:00:17.100
All hands turn to, readying the boats for the water.

00:00:17.100 --> 00:00:25.100
Sails come out, lines are sorted, and everything is checked twice.

00:00:25.100 --> 00:00:33.100
The mainsail climbs the mast, and the boat comes alive.

00:00:33.100 --> 00:00:37.100
Smiles all around — this is what we came for.

00:00:37.100 --> 00:00:45.100
One by one, we step aboard and find our places.

00:00:45.100 --> 00:00:55.100
Out on the water, a young sailor takes the helm, the instructor right alongside.

00:00:55.100 --> 00:00:59.400
Hands on the tiller, eyes on the sails, sailing the boat.

00:00:59.400 --> 00:01:03.400
Around us, the bay is alive with boats under sail.

00:01:03.400 --> 00:01:11.400
We glide down the estuary under a wide blue sky.

00:01:11.400 --> 00:01:16.700
A fine day on the water, harnessing the wind — the whole point of BlindSail.
